# Gitflow Workflow (Mandatory)

Follow the Gitflow model from Atlassian's Gitflow tutorial, mapped to this
ecosystem's branch names in `ops/policies.yaml`.

Reference: https://www.atlassian.com/git/tutorials/comparing-workflows/gitflow-workflow

## Branch Roles

| Gitflow role | Sibling implementation repos | neuriplo-platform |
|--------------|------------------------------|-------------------|
| Production / release history | `master` | `main` |
| Integration | `develop` | n/a (use `main`) |
| Feature work | `feat/*`, `feature/*` from `develop` | short-lived branch from `main` if needed |
| Release prep | `release/*` from `develop` | n/a |
| Production hotfix | `hotfix/*` from `master` | hotfix branch from `main` |

## Required Flow

1. **Features**: branch from `develop`, merge back to `develop` only. Never merge
   feature work directly into `master` / platform `main`.
2. **Releases**: branch `release/*` from `develop`; when ready, merge into both
   `master` and `develop`; tag the release on `master`.
3. **Hotfixes**: branch from `master` (or platform `main`); merge into both
   `master` and `develop` when complete; tag on `master`.
4. **Platform docs/contracts**: normal work stays on `main` or a branch targeting
   `main`. Do not use sibling `develop`/`master` naming in `neuriplo-platform`.

## Before Every Commit, Push, or PR

1. Confirm the current branch matches the change type (feature / release / hotfix / platform).
2. Confirm the target branch is allowed:
   - sibling normal work -> `develop` (or `feat/*` / `feature/*`)
   - sibling release -> `master` via release/hotfix flow only
   - platform -> `main`
3. Never push normal development work directly to sibling `master`.
4. Never force-push to `main` or `master`.
5. Run repo-local validation before commit (`scripts/check_platform.py` here;
   owning-repo tests/build in implementation repos).
6. Only commit or push when the user explicitly asks.

## Default Commands (sibling feature work)

```bash
git checkout develop
git pull origin develop
git checkout -b feat/short-description
# work, validate, commit
git push -u origin feat/short-description
# open PR -> develop
```
